gomodel:SYNGO_787  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper charactrerizes EAAT4 as a L-glutamate and L-aspartate transporter that shuttles these across membranes in a sodium-dependent manner.\n\nTable 1 summarized the results of an 3H-L-glutamate and 3H-L-aspartate uptake assays in Xenopus oocytes expressing the transporter. Injected oocytes had a 30-fold higher uptake of the compounds than uninjected controls.. Experimental description: '... were used to amplify complementary DNAs from human cerebellar messenger RNA.'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-25" ;
